{"schema": 1, "document_id": "02--baystate-case-study-021624", "pattern_id": "patt_25f00c2e6e30", "decision": "wrong_type", "reviewer": "owner", "reviewed_at": "2026-07-02T16:41:11.284988+00:00", "pattern_type": "quotation", "notes": "Scare quotes / term-of-art, not an attributed quotation: quoted span is a NAME for something (a way of saying), no speaker, no attribution verb. speaker_name:null was the available signal. Registry needs a negative indicator separating speech quotes from scare quotes (short span + no attribution context + often title-case term)."}
