{"schema": 1, "document_id": "02--baystate-case-study-021624", "pattern_id": "patt_45b73fa7ceaf", "decision": "wrong_type", "reviewer": "owner", "reviewed_at": "2026-07-02T16:43:53.825064+00:00", "pattern_type": "quotation", "notes": "Not speech — this is a MISSION STATEMENT quoted inline (…its overall mission \"to improve the health…\"). speaker_name:null again. Two registry actions: (1) quotation negative indicator: quoted span introduced by a naming phrase (its mission / known as / so-called / titled) is not an attributed quote; (2) NEW pattern type worth adding: mission_statement (Layer 1) — lead-in contains mission/vision/values + org as subject; component candidates: mission callout / about-block. Second speaker_name:null false positive today — absence of a speaker should already damp quotation confidence."}
